--------------------------------------------Use Below Steps to create EKS cluster--------------------------------------
Select EKS in AWS console - create cluster
Create IAM Role
Create Cluster (AmazonEKSClusterPolicy)

Aws cli:

curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip" 
yum install unzip -y
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install
/usr/local/bin/aws --version
aws --version
aws configure

aws configure:
Access Key -Create

aws configure list-profiles
aws sts get-caller-identity

Kubectl install:
curl -o kubectl https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/amazon-eks/1.23.7/2022-06-29/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl
openssl sha1 -sha256 kubectl
chmod +x ./kubectl
mkdir -p $HOME/bin && cp ./kubectl $HOME/bin/kubectl && export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/bin
kubectl version --short --client

Cluster Setup

aws eks --region ap-south-1 describe-cluster --name My_TestCluster --query cluster.status
aws eks --region ap-south-1 update-kubeconfig --name My_TestCluster
aws eks list-clusters

worker node IAM roles
IAM Roles:
* AmazonEKS_CNI_Policy
* AmazonEKSworkernodepolicy
* AmazonEC2ContainerRegistryReadOnly


